      <h2 id="info-we-collect" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-2">1) Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect information in three ways: you provide it to us, we collect it automatically, and we receive it
        from third parties.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account & Profile:</strong> name, email, phone, organization, role, credentials you upload.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> device/browser, IP address, pages viewed, time on page, crash logs.</li>
        <li><strong>Cookies & Similar:</strong> session identifiers, auth tokens, analytics.</li>
        <li><strong>Payments (if applicable):</strong> billing contact and tokenized payment details (processed by our
          PCI-compliant provider; we don't store raw card numbers).</li>
        <li><strong>Third Parties:</strong> SSO identity providers (e.g., name, email), analytics platforms.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="how-we-use" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-4">2) How We Use Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide, secure, and improve the service (including troubleshooting and support).</li>
        <li>Authentication and authorization (including SSO, MFA).</li>
        <li>Personalize features, dashboards, and communications.</li>
        <li>Usage analytics and product research (aggregated/anonymous where possible).</li>
        <li>Legal compliance, fraud prevention, and enforcing terms.</li>
        <li>Marketing communications with your consent (you can opt out anytime).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="legal-bases" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-4">3) Legal Bases (GDPR/UK GDPR)</h2>
      <p>Our processing relies on: <em>performance of a contract</em>, <em>legitimate interests</em> (e.g., securing
        and improving the service), <em>consent</em> (for certain marketing/cookies), and <em>legal obligations</em>.
      </p>

      <h2 id="sharing" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-4">4) How We Share Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell personal information. We share it with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Service Providers/Sub-processors:</strong> hosting, email, analytics, payments, error monitoring
          (bound by contracts and confidentiality).</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliates and corporate transactions:</strong> in mergers, acquisitions, or asset transfers.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal & safety:</strong> to comply with law or protect rights, safety, and security.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="cookies" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-4">5) Cookies & Tracking</h2>
      <p>We use strictly necessary cookies (for login/session) and, with consent where required, analytics/functional
        cookies. You can manage preferences in your browser or via our cookie banner.</p>

      <h2 id="retention" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-4">6) Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We keep personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes above, then delete or anonymize it
        per our retention schedule and applicable laws.</p>

      <h2 id="security" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-4">7) Security</h2>
      <p>We employ administrative, technical, and physical safeguards appropriate to the nature of the data and risks,
        including encryption in transit, access controls, and monitoring. No method is 100% secure.</p>

      <h2 id="intl" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-4">8) International Transfers</h2>
      <p>Where data moves across borders, we use appropriate safeguards (e.g., Standard Contractual Clauses) and limit
        access to what's necessary.</p>

      <h2 id="rights" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-4">9) Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or port your data; to object or
        restrict processing; and to withdraw consent. You also may have the right to lodge a complaint with a
        supervisory authority.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>EU/UK:</strong> GDPR data subject rights.</li>
        <li><strong>California:</strong> CCPA/CPRA rights (access, delete, correct, opt-out of “sale/share”).</li>
        <li><strong>Other regions:</strong> We honor local laws where applicable.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="small">To exercise rights, <a href="/contact">
          Contact us
        </a>. We may verify your request.</p>

      <h2 id="children" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-4">10) Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>Our services are not directed to children under 13 (or as defined by local law). We do not knowingly collect
        such data. If you believe a child provided personal information, contact us to remove it.</p>

      <h2 id="changes" class="section-title h4 fw-bold mt-4">11) Changes to this Policy</h2>
